[SN]TITLE[SN]
Rio Olympics 2016: Australia's Mack Horton wins men's 400m freestyle

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Australian swimmer Mack Horton held off the challenge of 2012 champion Sun Yang over the final 50m to win the Olympic men's 400m freestyle.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is not supported on this device
Horton finished in a time of three minutes 41.55 seconds, as China's Sun took silver in 3:41.68 and Italy's Gabriele Detti won bronze.
Briton James Guy led for more than 250m before fading and finishing sixth.
"In the last 100m or so I could see Sun and Mack going past and I thought, 'Oh no'," Guy told BBC Sport.
